   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/gillis/Long_Floyd_&amp;_Margery.pdf">Floyd and Margery Long recount memories of Gillis Long's life as well as reading
            from his letters. They discuss the history of the Long family, growing up in Winn Parish
            during the Depression, Gillis Long's attendance and political campaigning at Louisiana
            State University, his service in Europe during World War II, his relationships with Earl
            and Russell Long, his close ties to black voters, his health problems, Catherine Long's
            political participation, and Gillis Long's political career.</abstract>
